<H1>Regular expressions</H1>

<P>A regular expression is a concise way of expressing any
pattern of characters.</P>

<P>You construct a regular expression by combining ordinary
characters with one or more metacharacters: characters
that have special meaning for the
 <A HREF="../glossary/gs.html#shell">shell</A>.</P>

<P>Regular expressions can be used to:</P>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="regexp1.html">specify filenames</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="../utilities2/grep3.html">search file contents</A></LI>
<LI>change file contents</LI>
</UL>

<P>Commands differ in the range of the regular expressions
that they support. Check the <A HREF="../manual/index.html">manual page</A>
 for the command for further details.</P>

